\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 12, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ngv1688454370143.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ngv1688454370143.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ngv1688454370143.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"mjy1665702614205\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                     \n Label\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">A label displays text on a component, such as the name of an associated field or an instruction to the user.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"mjy1665702614205__section_w8567ab1b5b1_w8568ab1b5_w8569ab1\">\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"mjy1665702614205__table_d13448e1_d13449e1_d13450e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Widget Overview</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">Logical Widget Name:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">Label</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">Physical Widget Definition:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">ulabel</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">Triggers:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">Labels do not have triggers.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">Supported in Grid?</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">No</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">Supports Accessibility?</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes, for testing purposes and screen readers only. For more information,\n                           see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"abr1688541158363.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/abr1688541158363.html\" title=\"Uniface exposes the UI of generated Windows desktop applications to screen readers and automation tools for a number of widgets. By exposing the underlying infrastructure, screen readers and automated testing tools can target supported UI elements, and retrieve information regarding their name, value, and status. For these purposes, a mixture of two different technologies has been used - UI Automation and MSAA (Microsoft Active Accessibility).\">Accessibility</a>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"mjy1665702614205__section_w8570ab1b5b3_w8571ab1b5_w8572ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d519500e155\">\n                       \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mjy1665702614205__p_d113015e1_d113016e1_d113017e1\">Labels are treated as widgets because they physically represent a development object on a component, just as widgets represent fields. However, you cannot give them logical names and their properties are not dynamic. Only the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Label Text</span> property can be set in ProcScript (using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$labelproperties</span>).</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mjy1665702614205__p_d113018e1_d113019e1_d113020e1\">For Form and Report components, the default values for <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Transparency</span> and <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Default Font</span> properties can be set in the application's <span class=\"ph filepath\">.ini</span> file. Use the following line in your <span class=\"ph filepath\">.ini</span> file to control transparency and font for all labels:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">.L=ulabel(transparency=on;labelfont=label)</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mjy1665702614205__p_d113021e1_d113022e1_d113023e1\">If transparency is not specified, the default is <code class=\"ph codeph\">Off</code>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mjy1665702614205__p_d113024e1_d113025e1_d113026e1\">If a label is not completely filled and its background color matches that of the component, Uniface reduces the label to fit the text, exposing any borders otherwise covered by the field. Uniface does not shrink labels that do not meet these criteria, so borders could be obscured, even though the contents of the fields fit within the borders.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mjy1665702614205__p_d113027e1_d113028e1_d113029e1\">In character mode, labels are not supported but are mapped to background text.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"mjy1665702614205__section_w8573ab1b5b5_w8574ab1b5_w8575ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d519500e201\">\n                       \n Label Properties\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mjy1665702614205__li_d43427e1_d43428e1_d43429e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"asq1665702609631.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/asq1665702609631.html\" title=\"Horizontal alignment of the label—Left, Right, or Center.\">Horizontal Alignment</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mjy1665702614205__li_d43430e1_d43431e1_d43432e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rjx1665702609708.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rjx1665702609708.html\" title=\"Vertical alignment of the label— Top(default), Bottom, or Center.\">Vertical Alignment</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mjy1665702614205__li_d43433e1_d43434e1_d43435e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kvj1665702609788.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kvj1665702609788.html\" title=\"Determines whether the widget is transparent.\">Transparency</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mjy1665702614205__li_d43436e1_d43437e1_d43438e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"thz1665702609551.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/thz1665702609551.html\" title=\"Font to use for the label, and for tool tip text for widgets (if they support tool tips). The listed fonts are determines by the application's .ini file.\">Label Font</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mjy1665702614205__li_d43439e1_d43440e1_d43441e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jwc1665702609865.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jwc1665702609865.html\" title=\"Determines whether the label is repeated when multiple occurrences are drawn. Valid values are Do no repeat (default), Repeat if not empty, or Repeat.\">Repetition</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mjy1665702614205__li_d43442e1_d43443e1_d43444e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xcr1665702586927.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xcr1665702586927.html\" title=\"Text of the label. If the label is attached to a field, it can be set in ProcScript using the $labelproperties function.\">Label Text</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mjy1665702614205__li_d43445e1_d43446e1_d43447e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wwg1665702587409.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wwg1665702587409.html\" title=\"Code that identifies a Uniface index color, which represents a combination of background and foreground colors. Applicable only to Form components. Deprecated.\">Index Color</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mjy1665702614205__li_d43448e1_d43449e1_d43450e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fcv1665702609942.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fcv1665702609942.html\" title=\"Determines whether the background and foreground colors of the parent entity or form can be inherited. This property can be set in ProcScript for the widgets, but not for labels. Valid Values are True or False (default).\">Inherit Colors (InheritColors)</a> (<span class=\"ph filepath\">.ini</span> file only)\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mjy1665702614205__li_d43451e1_d43452e1_d43453e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kyj1665702610018.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kyj1665702610018.html\" title=\"Determines whether a label moves with its associated field when the field is repositioned.\">Anchor</a> (<span class=\"ph filepath\">.ini</span> file only)\n </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ifp1665702614021.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Labels in Forms and Reports</a><p>Labels are objects that contain static. Most labels are associated with a field, but unassociated labels can be used for any static text on the component.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mev1718887187681.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$labelproperties</a><p>Get and set the text of an associated label in a Form.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_4399951\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_4399951\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Label Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 12, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Label A label displays text on a component, such as the name of an associated field or an instruction to the user. Table 1. Widget Overview Logical Widget Name: Label Physical Widget Definition: ulabel Triggers: Labels do not have triggers. Supported in Grid? No Supports Accessibility? Yes, for testing purposes and screen readers only. For more information, see Accessibility . Description Labels are treated as widgets because they physically represent a development object on a component, just as widgets represent fields. However, you cannot give them logical names and their properties are not dynamic. Only the Label Text property can be set in ProcScript (using $labelproperties ). For Form and Report components, the default values for Transparency and Default Font properties can be set in the application's .ini file. Use the following line in your .ini file to control transparency and font for all labels: .L=ulabel(transparency=on;labelfont=label) Copy If transparency is not specified, the default is Off . If a label is not completely filled and its background color matches that of the component, Uniface reduces the label to fit the text, exposing any borders otherwise covered by the field. Uniface does not shrink labels that do not meet these criteria, so borders could be obscured, even though the contents of the fields fit within the borders. In character mode, labels are not supported but are mapped to background text. Label Properties Horizontal Alignment Vertical Alignment Transparency Label Font Repetition Label Text Index Color Inherit Colors (InheritColors) ( .ini file only) Anchor ( .ini file only) Related Links Labels in Forms and Reports Labels are objects that contain static. Most labels are associated with a field, but unassociated labels can be used for any static text on the component. $labelproperties Get and set the text of an associated label in a Form. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}